(***********************************************************************     *)
(* The specification of the Voucher Transfer protocol. This is a         *)
* two-phase commit protocol, in which a VTP (Voucher Transaction          *)
* Provider) coordinates "Source" and "Destination" voucher holders      *)
(SHs and DHs). SHs spontaneously issue Prepared messages. We ignore    *)
the Prepare messages that the VTP can send to the SHs and DHs. Such a  *)
message would cause the VTP to abort the transaction, an event         *)
represented here by the VTP spontaneously deciding to abort.           *)
************************************************************************)
(***********************************************************************     *)
(* Note: The RFC does not differentiate between a Holder who is        *)
* initiating the transfer (i.e. the holder of the voucher) and the    *)
* Holder who is receiving the voucher (i.e. the holder who would be   *)
* the future owner of this voucher). In order to make this distinction  *)
* we have the "Source" Voucher Holders (SHs), a subset of Holders     *)
* who would like to transfer an existing voucher they are "holding".    *)
* We also have the "Destination" Voucher Holders (DHs), a subset of  *)
* Holders who would like to receive the transferred         *)
* voucher. The set msgs contains just a single copy of such  *)
* a message.                                                    *)
************************************************************************)
(***********************************************************************     *)
(* Receipt of the same message twice is therefore allowed; but in   *)
this particular protocol, that's not a problem.                 *)
************************************************************************)
(***********************************************************************     *)
(* Source Voucher holder sh prepares.                              *)
* This action enables the SH to start sending Prepared messages  *)
* to the VTP and DHs.                                               *)
************************************************************************)
(***********************************************************************     *)
(* Destination Voucher holder dh prepares.                           *)
* This action enables the DH to start sending Prepared messages  *)
* to the VTP and SHs.                                               *)
************************************************************************)
(***********************************************************************)     *)
(* Source Voucher holder sh spontaneously decides to abort. As noted   *)
above, sh does not send any message in our simplified spec.          *)
* This action enables the SH to start sending Abort messages to  *)
* the VTP and DHs.                                                *)
************************************************************************)
(***********************************************************************)     *)
(* Destination Voucher holder dh spontaneously decides to abort. As   *)
noted above, dh does not send any message in our simplified spec.    *)
* This action enables the DH to start sending Abort messages to  *)
* the VTP and SHs.                                                *)
************************************************************************)
(***********************************************************************)     *)
(* Source Voucher holder sh is told by the VTP to Transfer.          *)
* This action enables a SH to transfer its voucher (i.e., send it   *)
* to another Holder).                                              *)
************************************************************************)
(***********************************************************************)     *)
(* Destination Voucher holder dh is told by the VTP to Transfer.       *)
* This action enables a DH to receive its voucher (i.e., accept it  *)
* from another Holder).                                            *)
************************************************************************)
(***********************************************************************)     *)
(* Source Voucher holder sh is told by the VTP to abort.              *)
* This action enables a SH to cancel its transfer (i.e., send an    *)
* Abort message).                                                *)
************************************************************************)
(***********************************************************************)     *)
(* Destination Voucher holder dh is told by the VTP to abort.           *)
* This action enables a DH to cancel its transfer (i.e., send an    *)
* Abort message).                                                *)
************************************************************************)
(***********************************************************************)     *)
(* A state predicate asserting that a SH and an DH have not reached   *)
conflicting decisions. It is an invariant of the specification.    *)
* This action enables the VTP to check if there are conflicting      *)
* decisions among the SHs and DHs, in which case it aborts         *)
* all transfers.                                                *)
************************************************************************)
(***********************************************************************)     *)
(* The complete spec of the a Voucher Transfer using Two-Phase  *)
commit protocol.                                                    *)
* This theorem asserts that the specification satisfies all       *)
* temporal formulas in its refinement, i.e., it is correct.        *)
************************************************************************)
====